 printed cost of 3 or less and put it into play. Shuffle your deck and flip this card over.\n<b>Side B</b>\nInto the West is immune to the effects of other cards and cannot leave your control or leave play. Allies you play from your hand cannot have their cost reduced by more than 2.\n<b>Forced</b>: At the beginning of the quest phase, attach Into the West to an ally you control, if able.\n<b>Forced</b>: At the end of the refresh phase, distribute X resources among heroes you control, where X is the attached card’s printed cost. Remove the attached card from the game and draw 1 card.','“I tried to save the Shire, and it has been saved, but not for me.” —Frodo Baggins, The Return of the King',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Donato Giancola','58d50ea3-ddb5-401d-9be0-58ddceac7112','2025-10-15 22:13:12','2025-10-16 14:24:15',0,'/bundles/cards/500042.png'),(1361,98,1,3,987,'500987','Frodo Baggins','Hobbit.','<b>Response</b>: After Frodo Baggins commits to the quest, spend 1 resource from his resource pool to ready another unique character committed to the quest. If you quest successfully this phase, reduce your threat by 1.','',1,NULL,7,2,1,2,2,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Lukasz Jaskolski','247bb211-bf15-4627-99e8-914a8f1ca1bf','2025-10-15 22:13:12','2025-10-16 14:24:15',0,'/bundles/cards/500987.png'),(1362,104,7,5,53,'501053','At the End of All Things','','<b>Side A</b>\nYou can only choose 2 starting heroes. They each get +4 threat cost, +1 [willpower], +1 [attack], +1 [defense], +1 hit point, and they each gain a resource icon matching the other hero’s printed sphere. They cannot gain resources from attachment card effects, and they cannot be healed.\n<b>Action</b>: Exhaust At the End of All Things to deal 1 damage to one of your starting heroes and ready your other starting hero.\n<b>Action</b>: Flip this card over. You cannot trigger this effect during the first 3 rounds.\n<b>Side B</b>\nYour starting heroes each get +4 threat cost, +1 [willpower], +1 [attack], +1